profile_positions.description:
Cleanroom engineer responsible for equipment maintenance and process development at EKL.

Representing EKL at EuroNanoLab Lithography Experts Meeting. 

Coordinator of the Safety and Introduction Course and Process Integration Training. 

Support the development of new processes as part of research and prototyping projects. 

Process engineer involved in 4"wafer small scale production. 

Equipment Engineering: 
• Responsible for process control and equipment maintenance of ASML Wafer Stepper, SUSS Mask Aligner, EVG Coater/Developer and EVG Spray Coating system;
• Preparation of equipment documentation, including standard operations procedures, protocols, reports; 
• Implementation of statistical process control in the lithography module;
• Data analysis and statistics for process improvement;
• Training of new users in different cleanroom equipment;
• Technical and technological troubleshooting.

Training: 
• Management of new participants (MSc and PhD students at TU Delft and external collaborators) in the Safety and Introduction Course;
• Safety and Introduction Course Trainer;
• Coordinator and Trainer of the Process Integration Course;
• Preparation of training material. 

Process Engineering: 
• Participation in the development of processes in accordance with customers requirements; 
• Support TU Delft students in optimizing the process; 
• Preparation of flowcharts and design of process cross sections; 
• Small scale production.

Software: 
• KLayout, Origin, Adobe Illustrator, Sketchup, Sharepoint

Specialist in lithography techniques, responsible for the Nanolithography bay at INL cleanroom, as part of the Microfabrication and Exploratory Nanotechnology group. 

Key Role: Engineer responsible for the Electron Beam Lithography (EBL) system (Raith EBPG 5200 ES 100kV) used for integration of microdevices in 200mm semiconductor wafers.

I have been involved in the following activities:

R&D Engineering: 
• Management of EBL through the implementation and development of novel processes;
• Introduction and validation of several chemical products for advanced R&D purposes;
• Development of micromachining process for replication using nanoimprint lithography;

Process Engineering: 
• Elaboration of official quotations for R&D projects; 
• Interaction with other INL groups, external collaborators and customers for product design and development; 
• Design of microfabrication process according to the customers specifications, including preparation of runsheets and design of process cross sections; 
• Development of microfabrication process as advanced operator of several micro and nanofabrication techniques in a cleanroom environment; 
• Data processing and analysis, reporting and shipping to the customer. 

Equipment and Logistics: 
• Equipment maintenance, including control routines and technical troubleshooting;
• Management of corrective and preventive maintenance actions with suppliers;
• Stock control of cleanroom consumables stock and supplies;
• Preparation of equipment documentation, including standard operation procedures; 

Training: 
• Tutoring and supervision of university students in cleanroom projects;
• Training of cleanroom process engineers and users in different equipment and techniques; 
• Technical and practical advice to internal researchers and external collaborators;

Software: 
• AutoCAD; KLayout; Origin8; Adobe Illustrator; Sketchup
